## Kubernetes secrets are created differently in SAP AI Core

You cannot create them via AI Launchpad UI directly. You need to use the **SAP AI Core API**.

---

## Create the secret via API call

Run this from your SAP BAS terminal:

### Step 1 — Get your token first
```python
import requests

CLIENT_ID     = "sb-524de71c-6fdc-42f9-9ca3-1aa049f9521f!b37640|xsuaa_std!b15301"
CLIENT_SECRET = "56e3a705-fe31-4cd8-adab-b9b49790abbe$VkGaPU4HAATczI9yH00PmPRSFS4QU-dJCJw9XzuED8o="
AUTH_URL      = "https://fin-analytical-svc-rnd.authentication.ap11.hana.ondemand.com"

response = requests.post(
    url=f"{AUTH_URL}/oauth/token",
    data={
        "grant_type":    "client_credentials",
        "client_id":     CLIENT_ID,
        "client_secret": CLIENT_SECRET
    }
)
token = response.json()["access_token"]
print("Token retrieved ✅")
```

### Step 2 — Create the Kubernetes secret
```python
import base64

AI_CORE_API   = "https://api.ai.prod-ap11.ap-southeast-1.aws.ml.hana.ondemand.com"
RESOURCE_GROUP = "default"

def b64(value):
    return base64.b64encode(value.encode()).decode()

headers = {
    "Authorization":     f"Bearer {token}",
    "AI-Resource-Group": RESOURCE_GROUP,
    "Content-Type":      "application/json"
}

secret_payload = {
    "name": "s3-credentials",
    "data": {
        "AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID":     b64("AKIAQAB2LD3UVWNB5D3E"),
        "AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY": b64("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"),
        "AWS_S3_ENDPOINT_URL":   b64("https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com")
    }
}

response = requests.post(
    url=f"{AI_CORE_API}/v2/admin/secrets",
    headers=headers,
    json=secret_payload
)
print(f"Status : {response.status_code}")
print(f"Response: {response.text}")
```

---

## Expected response
```json
{"message": "secret s3-credentials created"}
```

Once created, the secret `s3-credentials` is available in your `default` resource group and the serving YAML can reference it via `secretKeyRef`.

